title: Missing Foundation Discography
description:
Complete discography of multimedia collective Missing Foundation. Propelled by anarchist beliefs, they created politically-inspired music a` la David Peel and the Fugs that also borrowed from Foetus and Ministry. Their live shows were notorious for sparking civil disobedience (including the occasional riot) and causing serious damage to the venues at which they performed, leading the group to be banned from some cities entirely.

(1988) - 1933 Your House Is Mine
(1989) - Demise
